<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,569,739]" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,569,595]" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Description.</emphasis>
Vertex reddish yellow, with pair of dark spots near anterior margin surrounded with reddish luster (
<figureCitation box="[159,259,605,631]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,764,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-532@2.[151,1436,761,1755]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov.: 1 Habitus, dorsal view 2 Habitus, lateral view 3 Head and thorax, dorsal view 4 Face; 9 Fore wing 10 Hind wing. Arboridia (Arborifera) changlingensis sp. nov.: 5 Habitus, dorsal view 6 Habitus, lateral view 7 Head and thorax, dorsal view 8 Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141885" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141885/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
). Face milky yellow, sides of frontoclypeus with dark brown lines, anteclypeus brown (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1340,605,631]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,764,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-532@2.[151,1436,761,1755]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov.: 1 Habitus, dorsal view 2 Habitus, lateral view 3 Head and thorax, dorsal view 4 Face; 9 Fore wing 10 Hind wing. Arboridia (Arborifera) changlingensis sp. nov.: 5 Habitus, dorsal view 6 Habitus, lateral view 7 Head and thorax, dorsal view 8 Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141885" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141885/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Figs 2, 4</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with anterior margin yellow with paired dark brown spots, posterior margin pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1301,641,667]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,764,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-532@2.[151,1436,761,1755]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov.: 1 Habitus, dorsal view 2 Habitus, lateral view 3 Head and thorax, dorsal view 4 Face; 9 Fore wing 10 Hind wing. Arboridia (Arborifera) changlingensis sp. nov.: 5 Habitus, dorsal view 6 Habitus, lateral view 7 Head and thorax, dorsal view 8 Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141885" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141885/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
). Scutellum light orange, with basal triangles black (
<figureCitation box="[607,710,677,703]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,764,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-532@2.[151,1436,761,1755]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov.: 1 Habitus, dorsal view 2 Habitus, lateral view 3 Head and thorax, dorsal view 4 Face; 9 Fore wing 10 Hind wing. Arboridia (Arborifera) changlingensis sp. nov.: 5 Habitus, dorsal view 6 Habitus, lateral view 7 Head and thorax, dorsal view 8 Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141885" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141885/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
). Fore wing beige, with reddish and light brown stripes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1781,1805]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,764,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-532@2.[151,1436,761,1755]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov.: 1 Habitus, dorsal view 2 Habitus, lateral view 3 Head and thorax, dorsal view 4 Face; 9 Fore wing 10 Hind wing. Arboridia (Arborifera) changlingensis sp. nov.: 5 Habitus, dorsal view 6 Habitus, lateral view 7 Head and thorax, dorsal view 8 Face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141885" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141885/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Figs 1, 2, 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
