<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1923,2022]" box="[199,1116,1923,1950]" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">
Male abdominal apodemes extended beyond hind margin of 3rd sternite (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1102,1923,1950]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,501,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-151@3.[151,1436,489,1931]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov. 11 Abdominal apodemes 12 Pygofer, lateral view 13 Dorsal pygofer appendage, lateral view 14 Subgenital plate 15 Style 16 Aedeagus, lateral view 17 Aedeagus, ventral view 18 Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141891/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1923,2022]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,466]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="352" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,1959,1986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer dorsal appendage simple, expanded at base, narrowed at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1297,1959,1986]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,501,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-151@3.[151,1436,489,1931]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov. 11 Abdominal apodemes 12 Pygofer, lateral view 13 Dorsal pygofer appendage, lateral view 14 Subgenital plate 15 Style 16 Aedeagus, lateral view 17 Aedeagus, ventral view 18 Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141891/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Figs 12, 13</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with 2 macrosetae on lateral surface, and row of peg-like setae from subbase to apex, several microsetae scat- tered on apical portion (
<figureCitation box="[417,545,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,501,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-151@3.[151,1436,489,1931]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov. 11 Abdominal apodemes 12 Pygofer, lateral view 13 Dorsal pygofer appendage, lateral view 14 Subgenital plate 15 Style 16 Aedeagus, lateral view 17 Aedeagus, ventral view 18 Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141891/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Figs 12, 14</figureCitation>
). Style long, with 3 points apically, preapical point tiny and well separated from apical two, inner apical point distinctly longer than outer one; preapical lobe obtuse (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1188,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,501,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-151@3.[151,1436,489,1931]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov. 11 Abdominal apodemes 12 Pygofer, lateral view 13 Dorsal pygofer appendage, lateral view 14 Subgenital plate 15 Style 16 Aedeagus, lateral view 17 Aedeagus, ventral view 18 Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141891/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft slim, with pair of small lateral tooth-like protrusions apically, and single small ventral tooth-like process slightly basad of shaft midlength; preatrium shorter than shaft and dorsal apodeme expanded (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1170,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,501,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-151@3.[151,1436,489,1931]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov. 11 Abdominal apodemes 12 Pygofer, lateral view 13 Dorsal pygofer appendage, lateral view 14 Subgenital plate 15 Style 16 Aedeagus, lateral view 17 Aedeagus, ventral view 18 Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141891/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Figs 16, 17</figureCitation>
). Connective V-shaped, with two long arms, stem well developed (
<figureCitation box="[628,711,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–18" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[162,1431,501,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-151@3.[151,1436,489,1931]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11–18. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov. 11 Abdominal apodemes 12 Pygofer, lateral view 13 Dorsal pygofer appendage, lateral view 14 Subgenital plate 15 Style 16 Aedeagus, lateral view 17 Aedeagus, ventral view 18 Connective." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141891" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141891/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,404,330,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII with posterior margin convex in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1074,1205,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–26" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[160,1435,417,1946]" captionTargetId="figure-113@4.[151,1436,417,1958]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 19–26. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov. 19 Female pygofer 20 Sternite VII 21 Valvula I 22 Partial enlargement of valvula I 23 Valvulae II 24 Partial enlargement of valvulae II 25 Valvula III 26 Partial enlargement of valvula III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141893/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Figs 19, 20</figureCitation>
). Valvula I elongate, slightly broadened near apex, dorsal sculpture strigate (
<figureCitation box="[765,895,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–26" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[160,1435,417,1946]" captionTargetId="figure-113@4.[151,1436,417,1958]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 19–26. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov. 19 Female pygofer 20 Sternite VII 21 Valvula I 22 Partial enlargement of valvula I 23 Valvulae II 24 Partial enlargement of valvulae II 25 Valvula III 26 Partial enlargement of valvula III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141893/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Figs 21, 22</figureCitation>
). Valvulae II asymmetrical, with two blades, one of which has tooth-like protrusions (
<figureCitation box="[557,687,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–26" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[160,1435,417,1946]" captionTargetId="figure-113@4.[151,1436,417,1958]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 19–26. Arboridia (Arboridia) huajiangensis sp. nov. 19 Female pygofer 20 Sternite VII 21 Valvula I 22 Partial enlargement of valvula I 23 Valvulae II 24 Partial enlargement of valvulae II 25 Valvula III 26 Partial enlargement of valvula III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141893/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Figs 23, 24</figureCitation>
). Valvula III blade-like, with microtricha on margin and apex (
